metadata.name: Working Man
metadata.description:
1/1 

"Working Man"

This was taken on the streets of Japan. I had just landed in Tokyo the night before. Jetlagged, I decided to take a stroll around the hotel. It was 5 AM. The sun had just peaked over the tall, overarching skyscrapers and bled onto the street. I saw this gentleman walking towards me. He was heading to work. I think we could all relate to this man. Up before everyone else, paying the dues - hoping that one day it will all pay off. This photo is one of my favorite photos that I have captured during my time in Japan. 

My T:ME JPN collection is based on a series of photographs I've shot throughout my career as a freelance photographer. These photographs are 1/1 not because no one else has them but simply because it is a snapshot of a time that we can never get back.
